Package org.jsapar.schema

Contains classes that describes the input or output format.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CellValueCondition
    Interface for cell validation.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CsvSchema
    Defines a schema for a delimited input text.
    CsvSchemaCell
    Describes the schema for a specific csv cell.
    CsvSchemaLine
    Describes the schema for a delimiter separated line.
    FixedWidthCellPositions
    Contains positions within a line for a fixed with cell.
    FixedWidthSchema
    Defines a schema for a fixed position buffer.
    FixedWidthSchemaCell
    Describes how a cell is represented for a fixed width schema.
    FixedWidthSchemaLine
    This class represents the schema for a line of a fixed with file.
    MatchingCellValueCondition
    A CellValueCondition that matches based on a regex expression.
    Schema
    Abstract base class for all type of jsapar schemata.
    Schema2XmlExtractor
    Extracts xml representation for a Schema and writes it to a writer.
    SchemaCell
    Denotes the structure of one cell/column.
    SchemaCellFormat
    Describes the format of a cell when converted to or from text, including what data type that the cell is expected to have.
    SchemaLine
    Abstract base class that describes the schema for a line.
    Xml2SchemaBuilder
    Builds a Schema instance from xml that conforms to the JSaPar xsd.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    FixedWidthSchemaCell.Alignment
    Describes how a cell is aligned within its allocated space.
    QuoteBehavior
    Defines how to quote csv cells.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    SchemaException
    Exception used for when there are errors within a schema or while building a schema.

Package org.jsapar.schema Description

Contains classes that describes the input or output format.

See sample files in the samples folder of the project. The JUnit test org.jsapar.JSaParExamplesTest.java contains a more comprehensive set of examples of how to use the package.
